Enterprise Integration Metamodel
A Behavior-Based Governance Framework for Post-M&amp;A Banking Architecture

1. Executive Summary
As our banking ecosystem expands through M&amp;A and modernization initiatives, our
Architecture Review Board (ARB) processes must scale. Currently, integration governance
is highly subjective, often focusing on vendor tooling rather than architectural behavior.
This framework introduces a strict 6-Layer Enterprise Integration Metamodel. By
separating the &#39;Why&#39; and &#39;When&#39; of an integration from the &#39;What&#39; and &#39;Which tool,&#39; we
transition from subjective gatekeeping to objective, &#39;Paved Road&#39; governance. This
approach contains legacy technical debt, standardizes cross-core communication, and
accelerates time-to-market.

2. The 6-Layer Governance Taxonomy
Every enterprise integration must be classified across the following six distinct dimensions
before vendor tooling is selected:
